<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OPEC Oil Price Rebounds to 17.92 Dollars a Barrel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The average price of OPEC's basket
of seven crude oils rebounded to 17.92 U.S. dollars a barrel last
week but much lower than its benchmark price of 21 dollars, the
Vienna-based OPEC Secretariat announced today.
</P>
<P>
A week earlier, the average oil price was 17.15 dollars a
barrel.
</P>
<P>
In June, OPEC's average oil price was only 17.37 dollars per
barrel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
