<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Merger Activity Shoots up to Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Announced mergers in the United
States reached a record high of 366 billion dollars in the first
half of the year, up 16 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Today's Wall Street Journal quoted the Securities Data Company
as saying the dollar volume of mergers is up despite a declining
number of deals, indicating that transactions are getting bigger.
</P>
<P>
The first six months saw at least 74 transactions valued at 1
billion dollars or more announced in the United States, as against
49 in the same period last year, the newspaper report said.
</P>
<P>
Globally, merger activity rose to an equivalent to 692 billion
dollars in announced transactions, an 18 percent growth from the
same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
