<HEADLINE> Former Croatian Leader Dies Of Stroke </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Mate Boban, a leader of former
Croat Republic of Herceg-Bosna, died of a brain stroke early
today, local media reported.
</P>
<P>
Boban died in a hospital in the Croat-controlled western
Mostar, where he had been put under intensive care since Friday,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
Boban, who was Croatian president in 1993 when Croats fought
with their former Muslim allies, was reportedly responsible for
the ethnic cleansing in the Croat-controlled part of Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
He stepped down before Croats and Muslims agreed to form a
federation in 1994.  
</P>
</TEXT>
