<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Emir Receives Egyptian Parliamentary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Amir Sheikh Jaber
Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah today received a visiting Egyptian parliamentary
delegation and expressed wishes that Kuwaiti-Egyptian relations be
further developed, a statement by the Amiri Dewan (office) said.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian delegation headed by speaker of Egyptian Shura
(consultative) council Mustafa Kamal Helmi arrived here Sunday
on a friendly visit.
</P>
<P>
Helmi said upon arrival that his visit which was at the
invitation of the Speaker of Kuwait's parliament Ahmed Al-Sadoun,
aims at boosting bilateral relations at various fields.
</P>
<P>
Helmi is also expected to meet with Kuwaiti acting Prime
Minister and Foreign Minister Sheikh Sabah Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah,
Minister of Defense Sheikh Salem Al-Sabah and Minister of
Information Sheikh Saud Nasser Al-Sabah.
</P>
<P>
The discussions with Kuwaiti officials would cover the Mideast
peace process, Arab solidarity and the establishment of an Arab
common market, Kuwaiti official sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
