<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Set Up Economic Consultative Forum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean president Robert Mugabe
will launch the national economic consultative forum on wednesday
which will harmonise economic policy formulation, coordination
and development.
</P>
<P>
A government statement said today the aim of the forum would
be to create a "smart" partnership among the key economic players
in the public and private sectors, labour and other stake-holders
to enhance the economic development process of the nation.
</P>
<P>
Expected to attend are parliamentarians, non-governmental
organisations, researchers, multi-lateral agencies and
representatives of member countries of the Southern African
Development Community and Malaysia. 
</P>
