<HEADLINE> Road Accident Kills 10, Injures 12 in Kyrgyzstan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Nine Kyrgyz soccer players and an
international referee were killed in a road accident in southern
Kyrgyzstan, Interfax News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Caused by the overturn of the bus carrying members of the TFK
soccer team on a mountainous road and its plunge into a nearby
valley, the accident on Saturday also injured 12 others.
</P>
<P>
The injured players of the top-rated team, some seriously in
the head, were taken to a hospital.
</P>
<P>
The fatal accident, the third this year at the 71-kilometer
mark of the Osh road, was blamed on the poor road conditions
there, the Interfax report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
