<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Botswana Airlines Ready for Privatization: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Air Botswana General Manager
Joshua Galeforolwe said in Gaborone today that his company is
expected to start privatization operation in August.
</P>
<P>
"We were told by the government that as soon as we become
profitable, we would be privatized," the South African Press
Association quoted Galeforolwe as reporting.
</P>
<P>
According to Galeforolwe, Air Botswana recorded the first net
profit in March this year ever since it was formed in 1965.
Figures will be announced in August, he said.
</P>
<P>
Galeforolwe took the airlines from annual 20-million Pula
(5.77 million U.S. Dollars) losses to turning a profit in three
years after the government told him it was sink or swim and
refused further loans.
</P>
<P>
Galeforolwe said he had a plan for privatization ready to put
on the table. "We have been talking to many parties, including
the International Finance Corporation...They have made us a
proposal which we are taking up with the government," he said.
</P>
<P>
The general manager believes that it will be at least two,
maybe three, years before privatization can be concluded in his
company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
