<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Concerned About Fightings in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Russia is concerned about the
worsening situation in Cambodia and hopes the fighting factions
exercise restraint and settle their conflicts through peaceful
means, a Russian Foreign Ministry official said today.
</P>
<P>
After the fighting broke out on Saturday in Phnom Penh, Russia
lost contact with its embassy there, said the official.
</P>
<P>
The fighting from Saturday morning to Sunday evening between
forces of Cambodia's two co-prime ministers killed at least 10
people and injured more than 50 others in the capital city.
</P>
<P>
If the situation further deteriorates, Russia will not rule out
the possibility of evacuating all embassy personnel and citizens
out from Cambodia, the official told Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
So far, no Russians have been killed or injured in Cambodia,
said the Itar-Tass report.
</P>
<P>
The Russian government hopes that the international community
make joint efforts to bring the situation in Phnom Penh back to
normal, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
