in years early Monday morning in which rioters and police clashed
in Belfast, Londonderry and other towns after an Orange Order
march through a Catholic area of Portadown.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference, Mowlam said: "I understand the anger
there is in nationalist communities, but nothing justified the
orchestrated violence that we have seen in the last 24 hours."
</P>
<P>
