<HEADLINE> Malawi Foreign Minister Visits Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Malawi Foreign Minister
George Nga Ntafu arrived here today on an official visit aimed at
boosting political and economic cooperation relations between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
He was greeted at the airport by Kuwaiti Minister of
State for Cabinet Affairs Abdelaziz Al-Dekheel and other
governmental senior officials.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Kuwait, Ntafu will meet Kuwaiti Amir Sheikh
Jaber Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah and hold talks with his Kuwaiti
counterpart Sheikh Sabah Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah and Minister of
Commerce and Industry Jassem Al-Mudhaf, according to official
sources.
</P>
<P>
Malawi is a land-locked agricultural country located in
south-eastern Africa with tobacco, sugarcane and tea as its three
main economic pillars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
