<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Annual Inflation Rate Unchanged in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)'s annual
inflation remained at 1.5 percent in May, the same as in April and
well down on the 2.6 percent of May 1996, it was learned here
today.
</P>
<P>
The lowest rates were registered in both France and Finland
with 0.9 percent. The highest rate by far was Greece with 5.3
percent. Denmark and Portugal, both at 1.9 percent, were next
highest, according to Eurostat, the EU's statistical office.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rates fell to 2.2 percent in the United States,
rose to 0.6 percent in Switzerland and remained at 1.9 percent in
Japan.
</P>
<P>
The rate is according to the new European Index of Consumer
Prices, calculated as an average of the Harmonized Indices of
Consumer Prices of the EU member states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
