<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-07 19:53 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Welcomes Tajikistan Peace Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Turkey said today that it was
delighted to see the signing of a peace agreement which ends the
civil war in Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a regular press briefing here, Foreign Ministry
Deputy Spokesman Sermet Atacanli said that the signing of the
agreement was a big step toward restoring peace in Tajikitan,
which is regarded as "a brotherly country" of Turkey.
</P>
<P>
He said that Turkey hoped to see that the First Tajik National
Reconciliation Council meeting held in Moscow today would bring
stability to the war-torn country.
</P>
<P>
"Turkey has until now, and will continue supporting and
monitoring closely the developments and the peace process of
Tajikistan, " Atacanli said.
</P>
<P>
The general agreement was signed by warring Tajik parties on
June 27, ending the civil war since the former Soviet republic
became independent in 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
