<BODY>
<HEADLINE> European Shares Mixed, London Ends Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Shares on Europe's major stock
markets mixed today, with London ending marginally lower and
Frankfurt and Paris closing higher.
</P>
<P>
The London stock market was dragged down by a fall in futures
amid speculation that the newly-independent Bank of England would
raise interest rates this week to keep the economy from
overheating.
</P>
<P>
Britain's FTSE-100 closed at 4,810.7, down 2.1 points.
</P>
<P>
Germany's DAX index surged in late dealings to break 4,000
points as a firmer dollar and Wall Street gains gave the Frankfurt
market fresh energy as uncertainty evaporated.
</P>
<P>
The DAX-30 index closed at 3,972.84, up 30.31 points. In later
screen-based trade the IBIS DAX index ended at 4,003.35, up 56.62
points.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, shares closed 0.45 percent higher after a weaker
start as a stronger Wall Street canceled out the effect of an
easier dollar. The CAC-40 index closed up 13.18, at 2,947.66.
</P>
</TEXT>
