<HEADLINE> UN Mission to Withdraw From Angola if War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The United States' special
representative based in Angola Blundin Beye said here today that
if flames of war are reignited in Angola, the UN Observers
Mission will have to withdraw from the country.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks after just returning from Angola's central
city of Andulo, where he met Jonas Savimbi, leader of the
National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA).
</P>
<P>
The UN envoy said during their talks, the UNITA leader
promised that his movement will take its own responsibilities
under the resolution on the Angolan peace process passed by the
UN Security Council recently.
</P>
<P>
Beye added that he beleives next meeting between Angolan
President Eduardo dos Santos and Savimbi will be held soon in the
land of their own country.
</P>
<P>
He also conveyed a letter of UN Secretary General Kofi Annan
to Savimbi during their meeting on the oustanding problems in the
peace process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
