<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Army to Prosecute Soldiers Simulating War Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The German Defense Ministry said today
that it will prosecute seven soldiers who was recorded on an
amateur video simulating execution and rape of civilians during
trainings in preparation for a peace mission in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
The scandal hit the headlines during the weekend after the
Defense Ministry acquired the video showing scenes of brutal
execution and rape of civilians simulated by seven German soldiers
during a break in a normal training at the Hammelburg training
school in the southern German state of Bavaria in April 1996.
</P>
<P>
The soldiers were being trained in the school for deployment in
a peacekeeping mission in Bosnia, German media said. The video was
aired publicly on the German private television network Sat 1
today.
</P>
<P>
German Defense Minister Volker Ruehe has ordered "all necessary
steps" to clarify the case and to bring to account those
responsible, the Defense Ministry said today. Those involved in
the incident would be prosecuted for serious violation of their
duties, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
