<HEADLINE> Death Toll in Train Bomb Blast Rises to 33 in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- At least 33 people were killed
and 66 others injured, 30 seriously, in a powerful bomb explosion
that ripped through the compartment of a speeding passenger train
in India's Punjab state this afternoon, Press Trust of India
reported.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports had put the toll at 22.
</P>
<P>
The blast, set off by suspected militants, blew up the fourth
bogie from engine of the passenger train 40 minutes after it had
left Bathinda station of the northwestern Indian state at 13:20
hours local time today.
</P>
<P>
While 30 died on the spot, three succumbed to their injuries in
hospitals. Among the dead were six women and four children.
</P>
<P>
No group has claimed the responsibility for the blast, the
fourth in the state since February this year.
</P>
<P>
Indian ballistic experts were rummaging through the debris of
the mangled bogie to find out the nature of explosives used in the
blast. 
</P>
</TEXT>
