<HEADLINE> China Wins 9 Golds in Asian Weightlifting Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGZHOU, Southeast China, July 8 (Xinhua) -- China took nine
out of 12 gold medals at stake on the first day of the Asian
weightlifting championships here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Xing Fen of China, the 1990 Asian Games champion, swept three
gold medals at the women's 46-kilogram class. She lifted
105.5-kgs to break the clean and jerk world record of 105-kgs held
by her compatirot Guan Hong.
</P>
<P>
Xing won the snatch event with a lift of 75 kilograms and won
the total title with 180 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 50kg division, Chu Nan-mei of Chinese Taipei
swept the snatch, clean and jerk and total titles in 82.5, 100 and
182.5 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Yang Bin collected three gold medals from the men's
54kg category, beating Wang Huin-yuan of Chinese Taipei and Kim
Chol Min of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea into second
and third place.
</P>
<P>
In the men's 59kg class, Chinese made a clean sweep of all nine
medals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
