<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Urges Earnest Implementation of Grain Purchase Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- People involved in the nation's
grain production must make concerted efforts to purchase grain at
appropriate prices in a bid to protect the farmers' enthusiasm for
production and maintain the sustained development of agriculture
and the entire national economy.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji said this at a national video and
telephone conference here Monday.
</P>
<P>
China has seen a bumper summer harvest for the third
consecutive year, which has led to a drop in grain prices in some
places.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Rongji asked localities at all levels to publicize the fact
that the government will purchase the farmers' fixed quotas of
grain at the prices set by the State Council last year and
reaffirmed in a recent circular from the State Council. And the
grain exceeding the fixed quotas will be purchased at protective
prices, which refers to the standard prices set by the State
Council.
</P>
<P>
China has witnessed good harvests for several years running,
and the grain reserve is at an all-time record high. This is an
important guarantee for the sustained, rapid and healthy
development of the national economy, Zhu pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He asked the state-run grain systems to purchase grain at
protective prices and never reject, stop or restrict grain
purchase or give farmers IOUs.
</P>
<P>
Talking about how to increase the farmers' incomes and protect
their interests, Zhu said that the grain growing structure should
be rationally adjusted according to the market demand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
