<HEADLINE> More Funds Sought for Poor Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The General Office of the State
Council has issued a circular urging all provinces and cities to
provide more support for students with financial difficulties.
</P>
<P>
The circular says that aiding poor students is an important
task for colleges and institutes across the country, and
scholarships, loans, stipends and other types of funds have
greatly benefited students from poverty-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
It urges provincial and city governments to seek sufficient
funds to ensure that no college students have to drop out because
of financial difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Since 1994 the central government has allocated several hundred
million yuan to assist students who could not afford to pay their
tuition fees, according to the circular. 
</P>
