<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Exports 128,000 Tons of Coffee in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's coffee and tea
authority announced today that the nation exported 128,000 tons
of coffee in the newly-ended 1996/97 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
In a statement to local journalists, Abayneh Alemu, deputy
general manager of the authority said nearly 300 million U.S
Dollars has been obtained from the export of coffee which
accounts for 63 percent of the country's foreign currency
earnings.
</P>
<P>
According to the authority, over 165,000 tons of coffee were
supplied to the central market during the fiscal year which ended
on July 7, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia is a major coffee producer and exporter in Africa
with an annual production of over 200,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
In another development, a four-day workshop on the
implementation of the coffee extension program opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Opening the workshop, Beruk Debebe, chairman of management
board of the coffee and tea authority said the workshop is part
of the efforts exerted by the pertinent bodies to realize of
coffee policy which focuses among others on the promotion of
coffee production both in quantity and quality.
</P>
<P>
The workshop will assess internal and external economic
conditions expected to materialize in the coming three years and
suggest measures which should be taken with regard to coffee and
tea extension programs as well as production preparation and
marketing systems, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
