<HEADLINE> Norwegian Striker to Join Chelsea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Norwegian star striker Tore Andre
Flo has been cleared to move to English premier league club
Chelsea for the start of the new season, accorting to a report
from the Norwegian news agency NTB on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The London club have reached a financial deal to buy the
striker out of his present contract which is due to run until the
end of October, according to the NTB reports.
</P>
<P>
Flo's last match for Brann Bergen will be against Stromsgodset
in the Norwegian league on Sunday. 
