<HEADLINE> Takeover of MCI by British Telecom Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Justice Department of the
United States approved Monday British Telecom's acquisition of the
MCI Communication Corporation of the United States, thus clearing
a major regulatory hurdle for the acquisition of MCI, the nation's
second-largest long-distance telephone company only next to AT&AMP;T.
</P>
<P>
The London-based British Telecom and MCI Communications of
Washington announced their merger plan in November last year. In
May this year, the European Union cleared the deal valued at 22
billion U.S. dollars, subject to conditions to protect
competition.
</P>
<P>
The two telecommunication giants expressed confident that the
merger could be completed by fall this year, according to a report
of the New York Times.
</P>
<P>
The companies said that their proposed merger would benefit
consumers and businesses, creating competition that would bring
down phone rates on both sides of the Atlantic.
</P>
<P>
The combined company would rank second only to AT&AMP;T as a
long-distance carrier worldwide. It would have annual revenue of
about 43 billion U.S. dollars and business and residential
customers in 72 countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
