<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Cargo Ship Hijacked By Tamil Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) rebels have hijacked the civilian cargo ship "Morang
Bong' this afternoon in the north of Mulaitivu in Northern
Province of Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
The ship had been chartered by traders from Colombo to carry
essential goods to Point Pedro for civilians in the North,
military sources here said this evening.
</P>
<P>
They said the ship was returning from Point Pedro after
unloading its cargo. It was the second trip of the vessel to the
area.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have taken the ship to the Mulaitivu area and
at present it is anchored off the coast of Challai, over 200
kilometers from Colombo, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been waging a war for a separate state in the
north and east of the country since 1983. 
</P>
