<HEADLINE> Conference Calls for Strict Crackdown on Corruption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A conference held here today said
that government officials and members of judicial organs who are
involved in corruption should be punished severely.
</P>
<P>
From January to May this year 5,431 persons from Communist
Party or government organizations, administrative departments,
judicial organs and economic management departments, were
reportedly involved in crimes of embezzlement, bribery or
misappropriation of public funds, according to the conference.
</P>
<P>
Attending the conference was Zhang Siqing, procurator-general
of the Supreme People's Procuratorate. Chief procurators from
people's procuratorates at all levels were also present.
</P>
<P>
Liang Guoqing, deputy procurator-general of the Supreme
People's Procuratorate, made a speech at today's conference. He
stressed that a strict crackdown on corruption in administrative
departments and judicial organs is needed to maintain social
stability.
</P>
<P>
Since the fifth session of the Eighth National People's
Congress in February this year 212 people in procuratorates have
been dealt with for being involved in corruption.  
</P>
