<HEADLINE> 12 Dutch Tourists Killed in Road Accident in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Twelve Dutch tourists were killed and
13 others including Egyptians were injured today in a traffic
accident in southern Egypt, the Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred before noon when a tourist bus from the
southern archeological city of Luxor collided with a truck on the
Aswan-Abu Simble road, about 900 kilometers south of Cairo.
</P>
<P>
Governor of Aswan Salah Misbah announced a state of emergency
in local hospitals while five ambulances rushed to the scene of
the accident to transport and extend first aid services to
casualties.
</P>
<P>
The area is a famous tourist attraction featuring pharaonic
relics and spectacular landscape. 
</P>
