<HEADLINE> Leading Steel Producer Lists B Shares on Shenzhen Bourse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Benxi Iron and Steel Company
Ltd, one of China's leading hot-rolled steel makers, had 400
million B shares listed on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange today.
</P>
<P>
Nominally targeted for overseas investors and issued at a per
share price of 2.38 Hong Kong dollars, the shares collected an
equivalent of 968 million yuan for the company.
</P>
<P>
This fund, together with the more than one billion yuan pooled
from the listing of 120 million A shares not long ago, will be
injected into the company's technical renovation projects for
hot-rolled steel production.
</P>
<P>
The completion of such projects is expected to lift the
company's production capacity of steel products, and help increase
its share of the steel market.
</P>
<P>
Already the nation's fourth-biggest producer of hot-rolled
steel, Benxi is capable of producing 2.2 million tons of such
steel a year, with its sales accounting for 14.5 percent of the
nation's total.
</P>
<P>
The company made a profit of 488 million yuan last year, on an
annual sales volume of 4.95 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
