<HEADLINE> Inner Mongolia's First Expressway Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The first expressway in the Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region went into operation today.
</P>
<P>
It links this regional capital city with the region's major
industrial city of Baotou.
</P>
<P>
The 150.4-km expressway cost a total of 1.12 billion yuan
(about 120 million US dollars) and took four years to build.
</P>
<P>
The operation of the expressway is expected to boost the
development of the region's rich resources.  
</P>
