<HEADLINE> Ramos Orders Evacuation of Filipinos in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today ordered an immediate dispatch of at least one Philippine Air
Force plane to Phnom Penh to airlift Filipinos in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Ramos made the directive at this afternoon's weekly cabinet
meeting in the Presidential Palace, a news release from the palace
said.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Affairs Secretary Domingo Siazon has been instructed to
secure immediately the C-130 plane's landing clearance from
Cambodian authorities.
</P>
<P>
The plane will transfer the Filipinos to a nearby safe base
after which they will be brought back to the Philippines by
commercial aircraft.
</P>
<P>
Siazon said negotiation is under way with the Thai government
for any spaces available in Thai airliners to accommodate
Filipinos.
</P>
<P>
Siazon is scheduled to fly to Kuala Lumpur today for an
emergency meeting of the ASEAN foreign ministers where they are
expected to reconsider the Cambodia's entry into ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
Ramos also authorized the Philippine embassy to Cambodia to
bear the cost of food and other supplies for Filipino nationals
who may choose to stay on in Phnom Penh.
</P>
<P>
The president hoped that parties involved in fighting in
Cambodia would settle their disputes peacefully and avoid further
violence.
</P>
<P>
He called on the Cambodian government again to ensure the
safety of the estimated 500 Filipinos and other foreign nationals
in Cambodia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
