<HEADLINE> Democratic Alliance for Betterment of HK Celebrates Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic Alliance for
Betterment of Hong Kong held a reception here this evening to
celebrate the handover of Hong Kong to China and the 5th
anniversary of the founding of the Alliance.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the Alliance Tsang Yok Sing said at the reception
that since it was founded five years ago, the Alliance has devoted
to the smooth transition of Hong Kong and conducted research on
various issues concerning the handover and long-term development
of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said the Alliance is excited to see that the Special
Administrative Region (SAR) government has been operating very
smoothly, and Hong Kong remains stable and prosperous.
</P>
<P>
"The Alliance will continue to serve the prosperity and
long-term interests of the SAR, and continue to serve the overall
interests of the citizens," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive of the HKSAR Tung Chee Hwa, Commissioner of the
Chinese Foreign Ministry in the HKSAR Ma Yuzhen and some 300
other people attended the reception.
</P>
<P>
The Alliance was founded in July 1992, so far it has set up 12
branches and 10 district offices throughout Hong Kong, with over
1,300 members.
</P>
<P>
Tsang said the Alliance is committed to the construction of
Hong Kong and to the improvement of the people's
livelihood. 
</P>
