<HEADLINE> Malaysia Monitors Developments in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia is closely monitoring
developments in Cambodia, International Trade and Industry
Minister Rafidah Aziz said here today.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia has substantial interests in Cambodia both in terms of
the safety of Malaysians and the economic presence, the minister
said.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is the the biggest investor in Cambodia with 30
projects worth about 3.425 billion ringgit (about 1.37 billion
U.S. dollars), excluding the investment by YTL Corporation Ltd
worth 2.37 billion U.S. dollars at Siem Reap near Angkor Wat, she
said.
</P>
<P>
Most of the Malaysian investment in Cambodia are in
infrastructure development and upgrading, tourism, banking and
telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
"We would monitor the affects of the conflict on Malaysian
investments there," she said.
</P>
<P>
She said that the Malaysian government would take appropriate
steps to ensure that whatever problems arising from the conflict
on Malaysian ventures would be minimized. 
</P>
</TEXT>
