<HEADLINE> First World Record Falls in Asian Weightlifting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGZHOU, Southeast China, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese woman
Xing Fen set the first world record at the Asian weightlifting
championships here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 1990 Asian Games champion lifted 105.5 kilograms in her
second attempt to break the clean and jerk world mark of 105
kilograms held by her compatriot Guan Hong.
</P>
<P>
Xing also won the snatch event with a lift of 75 kilograms
before claiming the total title with 180 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
N. Kunjarani of India finished second by totalling 162.5
kilograms, followed by Tsai Hui-woan of Chinese Taipei at 155
kilograms. 
</P>
