<HEADLINE> Beijing Keen for Cooperation with Utah </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Beijing is expecting to increase
cooperation with the US State of Utah, said Jia Qinglin, the
city's mayor, during a meeting here today with a delegation led by
Governor of Utah Michaelo Leavitt.
</P>
<P>
The two sides signed a memorandum on economic cooperation here
yesterday, with the aim of helping promote bilateral ties and
exchanges in wider areas including software development, personnel
training and information exchange.
</P>
<P>
Leavitt said that an increasing number of entrepreneurs in Utah
show growing interest in cooperating with their Chinese
counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Jia said that Beijing is a center of high technology and has a
large number of professionals, giving it a good foundation for
bilateral cooperation and development.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will visit the north China port city of Tianjin,
Xi'an, capital of Shaanxi Province, and Guangzhou, capital of
Guangdong Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
