<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IASC Holds Meeting in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A meeting of the board of directors
of the International Accounting Standards Committee (IASC) was
launched here today.
</P>
<P>
All of the committee's 16 directors and observers sent their
representatives to the meeting, which was the first of its kind
ever organized by China since it joined the international
organization in May this year.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will cover a wide range of subjects, such as the
writing of financial statements, intangible assets, employee
welfare, financial instruments and business reporting.
</P>
<P>
An official of the accounting department of the Ministry of
Finance said that the meeting will play a positive role in
increasing exchanges and cooperation between China and the
international accounting community.
</P>
<P>
The IASC is a non-governmental organization founded in
1973. Its members, by June this year, included 120 professional
accounting organizations in more than 80 countries and regions.
</P>
</TEXT>
