<HEADLINE> 7 Killed in Road Accident in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed and
several others seriously injured today when a passenger van
collided with a truck in Pakistan's southern province of Sindh.
</P>
<P>
According to the Associated Press of Pakistan (APP), the van
was heading Sindh's capital of Karachi from Thatta, about 100
kilometers east of the port city.
</P>
<P>
It dashed against a truck near Gujo, 18 kilometer from Thatta
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The injured have been rushed to a health center, the APP said.
But it gave no message about the cause of the accident.  
</P>
</TEXT>
