<DOCNO> XIE19970708.0114 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Increase in Autumn Grain Production Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A national conference on agriculture
has urged all departments in charge of agricultural production to
spare no efforts to ensure another bumper harvest of autumn grain.
</P>
<P>
The conference, held in Zhangzhou City, Fujian Province, and
attended by Minister of Agriculture Liu Jiang and heads of
provincial-level departments of agriculture, asked the departments
to try their best to keep autumn grain production at the same
level of last year.
</P>
<P>
The officials warned of possible unfavorable weather conditions
for autumn grain production, even though a bumper summer grain
harvest has been registered in most parts of China.
</P>
<P>
Water-saving technology and dry-land farming techniques should
be widely adopted in north China, and the fine strains of grain
should be developed nationwide in order to improve the Chinese
people's diet, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
The conference urged the departments to attach special
importance to extending the term of farmers' land-use contracts
for another 30 years.
</P>
<P>
China started to carry out the "household contract
responsibility system" in rural areas in 1979. Under this system
farmers obtain farmland through land-use contracts and have the
freedom to grow various kinds of crops according to market demand.
</P>
<P>
The officials said the system is still a fundamental policy in
rural China, and should be adhered to.
</P>
<P>
The conference closed today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
