<DOCNO> XIE19970708.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Malaysian Supreme Head of State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
expressed his belief today that the China visit by Malaysian
Supreme Head of State Tunku Ja'afar would further increase mutual
understanding and friendship, and promote Sino-Malaysian
cooperative ties.
</P>
<P>
Meeting here this afternoon with Ja'afar, Jiang expressed his
thanks for Malaysia's support for China's resuming the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The grand ceremony for the return of Hong Kong proceeded very
smoothly, Jiang said, adding that Hong Kong's return to the
motherland was a major event in the Chinese people's political
life this year and was of far-reaching significance.
</P>
<P>
Jiang emphasized that China would unswervingly carry out the
policies of "one country, two systems", "Hong Kong people
governing Hong Kong" and "a high degree of autonomy", to maintain
the long-term prosperity and stability of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
China welcomes Malaysia to continue and enhance its exchanges
and cooperation with the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Ja'afar told Jiang that he had longed to visit China since he
was young. He was very much impressed by China's economic growth
and construction, he said. He added that he hoped that his current
China tour would give him a better understanding of the country
and its people.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian supreme head of state went on to say that the
friendly exchanges between the peoples of Malaysia and China have
a long history, and his current visit is aimed at boosting the
existing cooperative relations between the two countries,
especially bilateral trade ties.
</P>
<P>
Being a member of ASEAN, Malaysia will do its best to promote
the cooperative relations between ASEAN and China, he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China and Malaysia are good neighbors and the
two peoples enjoy a profound traditional friendship. The two
countries have witnessed increase in bilateral collaboration in
every field, he noted.
</P>
<P>
China attaches major importance to friendly and cooperative
ties with its neighbors and to the positive role of ASEAN in
maintaining regional peace and stability as well as promoting
regional economic cooperation, Jiang told Ja'afar, adding that
China hopes to further its friendly and cooperative links with
ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the meeting, Jiang presided over a welcoming ceremony
for Ja'afar.
</P>
<P>
Ja'afar and his party arrived here this afternoon for a state
visit as guests of Jiang. This is Ja'afar's first visit to China
since he took office as Malaysian Supreme Head of State in 1994.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
