<HEADLINE> Hohhot Airport Expansion Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Expansion work on the airport in
this capital city of the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region has been
completed, and a Boeing 767 passenger plane successfully landed on
the new runway today.
</P>
<P>
The project included the extension of a runway to 2,900 m, the
expansion of an airport lounge and the building of a new parking
apron.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the airport is now able to handle big aircraft,
such as Boeing 767s.
</P>
<P>
The expansion project was jointly launched by the CAAC and the
region last June, at a cost of more than 100 million yuan (about
12 million US dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
