<HEADLINE> HK's Dragonair Suspends Phnom Penh Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Dragonair, one of the two major
airlines based in Hong Kong, today announced suspension of service
to Phnom Penh, capital of Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
A statement by the company said: "Due to the closure of
Pochentong Airport in Phnom Penh, Cambodia, Dragonair flight KA
200 from Hong Kong to Phnom Penh and KA 201 from Phnom Penh to
Hong Kong which operate on Tuesdays and Saturdays have been
temporarily suspended."
</P>
<P>
"These services will resume when the airport reopens and the
airline is completely satisfied that it is safe to do so."
</P>
<P>
The airport has been closed since early Saturday when fighting
between troops loyal to one or the other of the country's two
prime ministers erupted in Phnom Penh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
