<HEADLINE> Choy So Yuk Elected Latest Member of HK PLC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The 400-member Selection
Committee today elected Ms. Choy So Yuk the latest member of the
Provisional Legislative Council (PLC) of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
Ms. Choy won 219 votes in the by-election to beat her two
another opponents Peter Wong and Leung Fu-wah, who were supported
by 118 and 39 voters respectively.
</P>
<P>
Thus Ms. Choy's election filled the vacancy in the 60-seat PLC
left by Maria Tam Wai-chu, who was appointed to the Basic Law
Committee of the HKSAR in late June.
</P>
<P>
Before the election, Ms. Choy of the Hong Kong Progressive
Alliance stressed the need for all the Hong Kong citizens to unite
in making further efforts to build Hong Kong into a new prosperous
region.
</P>
<P>
She described the "one country, two systems" policy as a
significant guarantee for the future stability and prosperity in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The Selection Committee consisting of representatives from
various circles in Hong Kong was set up last year for electing
HKSAR's legislators and Chief Executive.  
</P>
</TEXT>
