<HEADLINE> Malaysia, US Start Joint War Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia and the United States
today began a nine-day combined military exercise code-named "Ex
Carat 97", the Malaysian Defense Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
"Ex Carat '97" is being conducted at several locations in the
peninsula under the so-called "Cooperation Afloat Readiness and
Training" (Carat) program, it said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
A total of 3,000 Malaysian and US troops are taking part in the
exercise which altogether involved six separate exercises to be
conducted near east coastal cities of Kuantan and Mersing as well
as at the Army Training Center in Kahang and the Royal Malaysian
Navy (RMN) base in Lumut, northwest of the country.
</P>
<P>
The statement said "Carat 97" is aimed at evaluating both
forces' "Command and Control' systems and exposure to and
capability with weaponry.
</P>
<P>
Chief of warfare training of the Malaysian Armed Forces
headquarters Brig. Gen. Abdullah Ahmad launched the exercise at
the Tanjung Gelang naval base near Kuantan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
