<HEADLINE> NATO Leaders Approve Membership for Poland, Hungary and Czech </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, July 8 (Xinhua) -- NATO leaders today approved
invitations to Poland, Hungary and the Czech Republic to join the
alliance, Spanish news agency EFE quoted NATO sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The United States, with the backing of some European allies,
insisted that the first wave of eastward expansion should be
limited to the three countries.
</P>
<P>
But France, Italy and other allies wanted invitation also
extended to Romania and Slovenia, in an effort to avoid too heavy
a shift in NATO's future orientation toward Central Europe.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that the NATO leaders will announce the
invitation list later today at their summit meeting in the Spanish
capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
