<HEADLINE> Iran Launches T-72 Tank Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani today inaugurated the first phase of T-72 tank plant
in Dorroud, Lorestan province, west Iran, according to a Radio
report.
</P>
<P>
The state-run Tehran Radio reported that some 60 Iranian
industrial units are supplying the T-72 factory, which is located
some 420 kilometers southeast of the capital city of Tehran.
</P>
<P>
However, the report did not mention when and where the T-72
tank plant was imported. Specialists believe the plant was brought
in from Russia.
</P>
<P>
The tank, massively used by Iran's long-standing foe Iraq in
their eight-year war (1980-88), was then one of the most advanced
in the world.
</P>
<P>
At the ceremony today, Rafsanjani said that the tank production
line served as a significant step toward technology transfer and
strengthening of engineering design of Iran.
</P>
<P>
"This great service, which saves the country more than 1
billion dollar in hard currency, will have great economic
blessings for Iran," the Iranian president was quoted by the
report as saying.
</P>
<P>
He praised Iran's defense industry for its creativity, adding
that the manufacturing of T-72 tanks was among the greatest
dreams of the Iranian armed forces.
</P>
<P>
"The committed technicians of the defense industry are striving
to add another proud chapter to their history," he added.
</P>
<P>
However, the official news agency IRNA kept silent over the
inauguration of the T-72 plant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
