<HEADLINE> HK Property Prices Be Curbed: Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Local experts suggested that the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) government curb
soaring property prices in an effort to improve the business
environment and increase the competitiveness of Hong Kong economy.
</P>
<P>
Extremely high property prices may add the operational cost of
companies and increase inflation, experts attending a symposium on
the direction of the HKSAR's economic and social development, Wen
Wei Po reported today.
</P>
<P>
Some multi-national companies which have based their regional
headquarters here might be forced to move out if the rental prices
for office buildings were kept at a high level, they warned.
</P>
<P>
Experts pointed out that a huge gap between supply and demand
should be blamed for the ever rising real estate prices, and they
suggested that the HKSAR government increase the supply of land.
</P>
<P>
As the experts put it, promotion of high-tech industries and a
balanced development of the manufacturing and service sectors
would also increase the competitiveness of Hong Kong economy with
a perspective into the next century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
