<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Press Hails SAR's External Affairs Functions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Two of Hong Kong's major
newspapers published commentaries today, hailing the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) Government's being
authorized by the Central People's Government to handle certain
external affairs on its own.
</P>
<P>
The Commissioner of the country's Foreign Ministry in the
HKSAR, Ma Yuzhen, met with Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa
yesterday and passed on to Tung a letter from Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen which authorizes the HKSAR
Government to negotiate bilateral agreements with concerned
countries in five fields.
</P>
<P>
The authorization demonstrated once again the sincerity and
determination of the Central People's Government in implementing
the Basic Law, a commentary carried by Wen Wei Po said.
</P>
<P>
Article 13 of the Basic Law stipulates that the Central
People's Government shall be responsible for the foreign affairs
relating to the HKSAR; the Chinese Foreign Ministry shall
establish an office in Hong Kong to deal with foreign affairs; the
Central People's Government authorizes the HKSAR to conduct
relevant external affairs on its own in accordance with this Law,
said the commentary.
</P>
<P>
The authorization will benefit Hong Kong's high degree of
autonomy and its economic development and social stability, and
will also help safeguard the legitimate rights and interests of
the Hong Kong people, the commentary concluded.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Commercial Daily said that the meeting between Ma
and Tung marked the formal establishment of working relationship
between the Office of Commissioner and the HKSAR Government.
</P>
<P>
Ma described the relationship as that of mutual respect and
close cooperation during the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Upon the inauguration of the HKSAR Government, the Central
People's Government authorized the HKSAR Government to negotiate
bilateral agreements with concerned countries on air service
transit, investment promotion and protection, transfer of fugitive
offenders, transfer of sentenced persons and mutual legal
assistance in criminal matters.
</P>
<P>
This fully reflected the trust of the Central People's
Government in the HKSAR Government, said the commentary.
</P>
<P>
That the Office of Commissioner and the HKSAR Government make
good cooperation on foreign affairs of the HKSAR will accumulate
experience for the handling of foreign affairs under "one country,
two systems," and the experience is very significant to the final
realization of reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Ta Kung Pao carried a commentary today, titled "Sooner or
Later, Taiwan Will Embark on the Road of 'One Country, Two
Systems'."
</P>
<P>
The solution of the Hong Kong problem with the concept of "one
country, two systems" is very smooth and perfect, and it signifies
a vital step toward reunification of the motherland, the paper
said.
</P>
<P>
The principle of "one country, two systems" is applicable in
Hong Kong and, certainly, it will be applicable in Taiwan, it
noted, adding whether the Taiwan authorities are willing or not,
Taiwan will sooner or later take the road.
</P>
<P>
The smooth handover of Hong Kong demonstrates that the
principle respects both history and reality, gives good
consideration to the interests of all sides, and is the best way
to solve problems left by history, the commentary said.
</P>
<P>
It is foreseeable that the "one country, two systems" policy
will soon show its vitality in Hong Kong, setting a good example
for Taiwan, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
