<HEADLINE> Ramos Orders Halt of Offensive Against Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- President Fidel Ramos today ordered
government troops to cease from conducting offensives against
Muslim rebels in order to save the endangered peace process in the
southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Alexander Aguirre, head of the Presidential Management Staff,
said that President Ramos, through Defense Secretary Renato de
Villa, had directed the troops to hold on to their positions
instead of taking offensive actions.
</P>
<P>
But Aguirre said the military will also be forced to move if
the civilian population is threatened by the rebel Moro Islamic
Liberation Front (MILF).
</P>
<P>
He said government negotiating panel chairman Fortunato Abat
and Governor of the Autonomous Region of Muslim Mindanao Nur
Misuari are expected to establish contacts with MILF leaders for
the resumption of the peace negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Aguirre said Misuari has been authorized to talk with MILF
leader Hashim Salamat to bring back the MILF to the negotiating
table.
</P>
<P>
The MILF pulled out of the sixth round of low-level peace talks
with the government late last month after the military seized Camp
Rajah Muda, the second largest MILF headquarters in central
Mindanao, after two weeks of fierce offensives.
</P>
<P>
The MILF is a militant Muslim group which has sought to
establish an independent Islamic state in Mindanao. The MILF and
Manila started peace talks in January this year, but the talks
have been on-and-off for sporadic fightings between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
