<HEADLINE> China Concerned About Cambodia Situation: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman
Tang Guoqiang said here today that China is paying close attention
to the situation in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed that the Chinese Embassy in Cambodia will
provide consular protection to Chinese Hong Kong citizens stranded
in the Cambodian capital of Phnom Penh.
</P>
<P>
Responding to questions at today's regular press conference,
Tang said that, as a good neighbor of Cambodia, China has always
held that the parties involved should stick to the spirit of
national reconciliation advocated by King Norodom Sihanouk, and
strive to preserve the peace, stability and progress of the
country.
</P>
<P>
China sincerely hopes that the parties concerned will cherish
the maintenance of a peaceful situation and handle relevant
problems properly so as to prevent the situation from further
deterioration, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman stressed that the Chinese Embassy in Cambodia is
duty-bound to offer consular protection and services to Chinese
Hong Kong citizens in difficulty.
</P>
<P>
Since Hong Kong has returned to the motherland, Chinese
embassies and consulates will provide consular protection to
Chinese Hong Kong citizens in foreign countries based on the
Constitution, the Nationality Law and the Basic Law of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the protection of the legal rights and
interests of Chinese citizens and legal persons abroad is an
important task of Chinese embassies and consulates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
