<HEADLINE> Former President of Bangladesh Passes Away </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Former president of Bangladesh Abd
Sadat Mohamad Sayem died of old age this morning at his residence
here, according to an official handout available today.
</P>
<P>
He will be buried in the National Graveyard in the city today
while the national flag would fly at half-mast at all public
places to show respect to the former president.
</P>
<P>
Sayem, the first Chief Justice of Bangladesh, was sworn in as
the president on November 6, 1975. He served as president till
November 29, 1976 when then Chief of Army Staff Major General
Ziaur Rahman took over as Chief Martial Law Administrator.
</P>
<P>
Born in southeastern Rangpur district in 1916, Sayem had his
education in Rangpur Carmichael College, Calcutta Presidency
College and University Law College of Calcutta in India.  
</P>
