<HEADLINE> Indonesian, Thai Navies Hold Joint Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia and Thailand started a
week-long joint naval exercise in Surabaya, East Java, the Java
Sea, the Gundul Island waters and Jakarta on Monday, reports
reaching here today said.
</P>
<P>
The exercise code-named 'Sea Garuda 10-ab/97' is the follow-up
to the exercises held by the two countries so far which were aimed
at strengthening relations between the two countries, commander of
the Indonesian Eastern Naval Fleet Rear Admiral Bambang Surjanto
said when opening the exercise.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian navy has also held exercises with other
countries such as Singapore, Malaysia, Australia as well as the
United States.
</P>
<P>
About 367 personnel from the Indonesian navy and 223 personnel
from the Royal Thai Navy involved in the exercise.
</P>
<P>
It also involved two naval warships and one aircraft from
Indonesia and one frigate and a corvette from the Thai navy.
