the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index gained 9.24 points to close at 2007.23 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 170.61 million units,
valued at 429.85 million Singapore dollars (about 300.59 million
US dollars). Advances outnumbered declines by 174 to 157, while
297 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Mulpha Resources was the most actively traded stock as it
posted a turnover of 9.58 million units. It was followed by local
bookstore Popular which had 8.18 million shares traded. Van Der
Horst was next with 7.35 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Roth Malaya led the gainers of the day as it rose by 90 cents
to finish at 14.9 Singapore dollars. The Singapore Press Holdings
(SPH) Foreign gained 40 cents to end at 30.6 Singapore dollars,
while City Developments Warrant 98 and F&AMP;N closed 30 cents higher
at 11.7 and 10.7 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Thai Prime Fund was the biggest loser as
it declined by 80 cents to end at ten US dollars. Local car
distributor Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C) fell by 30 cents to close at
14.5 Singapore dollars, while Bukit Sembawang, Gentings, Malaya
Banking dropped by 20 cents each to finish at 25.8, 6.35 and 15
dollars respectively.  
