<HEADLINE> Soeharto Calls for Faster Asia-Europe Partnership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto has
called on the business communities in Asia and Europe to foster a
sincere and mutually beneficial partnership.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto made the remarks here today when he opened the first
Asia-Europe Business Conference. Some 450 representatives from 25
countries, namely 15 European Union members and seven ASEAN
(Association of Southeast Asian Nations) as well as China, Japan
and South Korea, are attending the three-day conference.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the meeting, the business communities of
the two continents will have a better mutual understanding for the
creation of a conducive environment for the intensified economic
and business relations among them.
</P>
<P>
"We are all preparing to enter a new era, characterized
primarily by the very rapid globalization process," he said.
</P>
<P>
To realize the people's well-being, he noted, it is a
prerequisite that there must be a partnership between the
government and private sector. This applies everywhere, whether in
the West or in the East, in the North or in the South.
</P>
<P>
The conference is a follow-up activity of the decision of the
first informal Asian-European Leaders Meeting (ASEM I ) in Bangkok
in March 1996.
</P>
<P>
The ASEM agreed to expand the opportunities for economic and
business cooperation through greater flow of investment, experts
and technology and generate faster two-way trade and investment
flows based on common commitment to market economy, open
multilateral trade system, non-discriminative liberalization and
open regionalism.
</P>
<P>
The conference is expected to discuss four issues, namely
developing small and medium size enterprises including supporting
industries; improving trade and investment facilitation and
infrastructure; future direction of Asia-Europe business
relationship and Asia-Europe business matchmaking for the common
good.
</P>
<P>
Some ministers from the Indonesian government and famous
businessmen will make speeches on economic cooperation between the
two continents.
</P>
<P>
The results of the meeting will be reported to the economic
ministers meeting to be held late September this year in Makuhari,
Japan and the second ASEM leaders meeting in London in Spring next
year.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto hoped the conference will become a forum for the
economic and business players from Asia and Europe to get in touch
with each other and foster a mutually beneficial cooperation
between the two important regions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
