<HEADLINE> GCC Invests Heavily in Petrochemical </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The overall investment in
petrochemical industry in the Gulf states is expected to rise to
33 billion U.S. dollars by 2000, according to a study issued by
the Gulf Organization for Industrial Consulting (GOIC).
</P>
