<HEADLINE> China's NPC Chairman Meets With Thai Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of China's
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, meeting with
a delegation of the House of Representatives of Thailand led by
First Deputy Speaker Mophon Phetsawang this afternoon, said that
China is willing to co-operate more closely with Thailand and
members of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that China and Thailand have enjoyed friendly
relations for a long period of time, and that co-operation between
the two countries has gone smoothly.
</P>
<P>
He noted that both China and Thailand hope to strengthen
relations on the existing basis and expressed the hope that China
and Thailand will co-operate more, with the development of China's
economy, particularly the further opening of southwest China.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Speaker told Qiao that he and other members of his
delegation feel "at home" when they come to China and that he
believes his visit will help further develop friendly relations
between his country and China.
</P>
<P>
He said the King and royal family as well as the Thai
government attach great importance to the development of
Thailand-China relations.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, speaking about the return of Hong Kong to China, said,
"We are very optimistic about the future of Hong Kong," and that
the "one country, two systems" policy, "Hong Kong people governing
Hong Kong", and the high degree of autonomy will be implemented.
</P>
<P>
"As long as the Basic Law is abided by, Hong Kong will have a
very bright future," Qiao remarked, adding that the return of Hong
Kong is important for China's relations with Thailand and ASEAN
countries.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Speaker said that the "one country, two systems"
policy begun by Deng Xiaoping is a model for solving problems left
over by history, and expressed the hope that Hong Kong will have
an even greater tomorrow after its return to China. He also wished
Macao a smooth return to China.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, who visited Thailand in 1993, asked the speaker to convey
his regards to Wan Muhammad Nor Matha, president of the Thai
National Assembly and speaker of the House of Representatives.
</P>
<P>
Wang Guangying, vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee,
was present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Thai delegation arrived in Beijing Friday at the invitation
of the NPC Standing Committee.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
