<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Investment Surges in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Investment in the Philippines in the
first five months of the year reached 10.27 billion US dollars, an
18 percent increase over the government target of 8.71 billion US
dollars, official statistics showed today.
</P>
<P>
Records from the Board of Investments showed that almost all
sectors of the country's economy recorded substantial increases
with the energy sector topping the list.
</P>
<P>
Some 2.56 million US dollars worth of investments out of 17
projects approved by the board were registered in the
energy-related sector, the data showed.
</P>
<P>
The infrastructure and industrial sector followed next with
1.95 million US dollars, a tremendous increase compared to the
174,920 US dollars recorded at the same time last year.
</P>
<P>
The manufacturing sector, which suffered a little setback, came
third with a total of 1.03 million US dollars. Last year, the
sector recorded some 1.09 million dollars with the construction
components obtaining the highest investment of 808,560 dollars.
</P>
<P>
The mining industry and the agriculture sector have also
recorded substantial increases, the record showed.
</P>
<P>
This is a clear indication that the country is continuously
enjoying the confidence of investors, both local and foreign, it
said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, more employment opportunities and quality jobs have
become available as the country's economy continues to grow.
</P>
</TEXT>
