<HEADLINE> Chinese Government Offers Grain Aid to DPRK Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government recently
decided to offer 80,000 tons of free grain as aid to the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK)
</P>
<P>
In recent years there has been a decrease in grain production
in the DPRK because of natural calamities and other reasons, and
grain is in extreme short supplies.
</P>
<P>
Some international organizations and countries have provided
humanitarian aid, and the Chinese government and people have paid
close attention to the situation and have felt sympathy for the
people of the DPRK and offered help for several times.
</P>
<P>
The 70,000 tons of grain as China's first free aid for this
year were transported to the DPRK on June 21. Proceeding from the
traditional relations between the peoples of the two countries and
from humanitarian reasons, the Chinese government has decided to
provide aid again to help the people there tide over the
difficulty of the current grain shortage.
</P>
<P>
The decision shows the consistent stand and desire of the
Chinese government to value and actively develop its traditional
friendly relations with the DPRK. 
</P>
</TEXT>
