<HEADLINE> Three Billion Yuan in Loans Granted for Shanghai's New Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A signing ceremony was held here
today for a three-billion-yuan loan from the State Development
Bank for Shanghai's Pudong International Airport.
</P>
<P>
This is the largest amount of money the State Development Bank
has put into Shanghai, and it is the largest civil aviation
project in China.
</P>
<P>
According to official sources, the new airport will cost 13.3
billion yuan, 3.6 billion yuan of which will come from the
municipal government and 40 billion Japanese yen from the Japanese
government.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Pudong Development Bank has provided 1.3 billion
yuan in loans for the airport, and will soon set up a branch
office there, sources say.
</P>
<P>
After the first-phase project is completed in 1999, the airport
will have an annual handling capacity of 20 million passengers and
750,000 tons of cargo, local aviation authorities say.
</P>
<P>
Its long-range goal is 70 million passengers and five million
tons of cargo annually, sources said. 
</P>
