<DOCNO> XIE19970708.0213 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: Publicizing Hong Kong Basic Law (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In Beijing, the law has been taught in primary and secondary
schools, and in Shanghai, university students made recordings of
the law and gave them to blind people. In Shangdong province, one
teacher, Li Chuanchen, wrote the full text of the law on a long
piece of silk and exclaimed proudly, "The return of Hong Kong is
the great concern of every Chinese."
</P>
<P>
Some misunderstandings concerning the handover were corrected
after the law was read by more people. A popular pop song at the
time says that after Hong Kong is returned every person in the
inland areas would be free to go to Hong Kong, but that is
something that is simply not in the Basic Law. Many people wrote
letters to newspaper editors criticizing the person who composed
the song.
</P>
<P>
Wu Jianfan said that the Basic Law is something of a
milestone: "The law relates to the smooth transfer and to the
long-term prosperity and stability of Hong Kong, to the
fundamental interests of the Chinese nation, and even to the peace
and development of Asia and the rest of the world."
</P>
<P>
"Publicizing the Basic Law on such a large scale shows the
Chinese government's sincerity and determination to implement
the 'One Country, Two Systems' policy," he added.
</P>
<P>
This is perhaps the reason why the law has been welcomed in
Hong Kong. One book on the law has been on the top-ten list of
best sellers in the region. And an education committee has set up
an eight-million-HK-dollar fund to publicize the law. It will also
be taught in Hong Kong's primary and secondary schools.
</P>
<P>
This enthusiasm has fueled a publicity campaign on the Macao
Basic Law, sources say. Macao will return to China in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, the first Chief Administrative Executive of the
Hong Kong SAR, said that the "One Country Two Systems" mechanism
will work successfully if the Basic Law is implemented well and
communications are improved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
