<HEADLINE> Sino-US Productive Forces Center Established in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- China's State Science and
Technology Commission (SSTC) and the state of Utah in the US
established a jointly productive forces center Monday in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
An official with the SSTC said the center's goal is to boost
economic and technological co-operation between enterprises in
China and the US, especially small and medium-sized ones.
</P>
<P>
The center will connect 1,400 high-tech companies or
universities in Utah and more than 60 productive force centers
under the SSTC and other research centers.
</P>
<P>
The official said the center will assist Chinese or American
ventures in entering each other's markets and will act as a
go-between in Sino-US trade, as well as run training classes and
help China's software products enter the world market.
</P>
<P>
Utah is the US's second largest state in software development.
</P>
<P>
Chinese State Councillor Song Jian, who is also SSTC Minister,
and Utah's Governor Michaei Leavitt attended the signing ceremony
for establishing the center, in the Great Hall of the People last
night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
