<HEADLINE> 4 People Killed by PKK in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Four people were killed and 10
others wounded Monday night when rebels of the outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK) attacked a minibus in southeastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Local press reported today that a group of PKK militants
strafed the minibus, killing four people including a girl.
</P>
<P>
The wounded people were taken to nearby hospitals in the
provinces of Elazig and Bingol for treatment, said the report.
</P>
<P>
It added that Turkish security forces have started a
large-scale operation in order to capture the PKK members that
escaped after the attack.
</P>
<P>
In another development, a group of extremists Monday attacked
a student dormitory, where Turkish troops were stationed, in
Niksar town of northern province of Tokat, wounding one policeman.
</P>
<P>
More than 24,000 people, including PKK guerrillas, civilians
and government troops, have been killed in conflicts since
August 1984 when the PKK started a separatist war for autonomy
in eastern and southeastern Turkey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
