<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five Arrested For Killing Sri Lankan Tamil MP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan Police Monday arrested
five persons suspected of having assassinated Tamil
Parliamentarian Arunachalam Thangathurai and four others at
Trincomalee on Saturday night, according to police sources here
today.
</P>
<P>
All five arrested persons are believed to be cadres of the
rebel Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) whom police say are
the masterminds behind the assassination.
</P>
<P>
Several clues on those lines have been uncovered, the sources
said, adding that "the style in which the attack was carried out
and certain other tell-tale signs will lead us to the culprits."
</P>
<P>
Thangathurai is among several leaders of the Tamil United
Liberation Front (TULF) who have been assassinated by the LTTE,
starting with the assassination of Jaffna Mayor Alfred Thuraiappah
in 1975.
</P>
<P>
The TULF, one of the mainstream Tamil political parties in Sri
Lanka, supports the ruling people's Alliance government.
</P>
<P>
TULF President M. Sivasithamparam has condemned the killing as
a cowardly and reprehensible act. He was an ardent supporter of
the peace process and had rendered enormous service to the Tamil
community in the process of settling the ethnic issue, said a TULF
statement issued on Monday.
</P>
<P>
All other Tamil political parties condemned the killing as a
cowardly act. The ruling Sri Lanka Freedom Party also condemned
the assassination. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
