<HEADLINE> Eds: Repeat with Correction hke --Albanian President Accepts Results of Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Albanian President Sali Berisha said
on Monday that his party would exist as a constructive opposition
party in the country.
</P>
<P>
Berisha made the remarks while meeting with Catherine
Lalamiere, general coordinator of the Organization for Security
and Cooperation of Europe and the Council of Europe, and Russell
Johnston, head of the delegation from the Parliamentary Assembly
of the Council of Europe. They came to Albania to oversee the
country's general elections in the past two weeks.
</P>
<P>
The Democratic Party accepted the results of the elections,
Berisha said, adding that it would be a constructive opposition
party and "would contribute to protecting people's freedoms, the
principle of democracy and the country's integration with Europe."
</P>
<P>
The leftist and central-leftist union led by the Socialist
Party of Albania gained more than 100 out of the 155 seats in the
parliament during the two rounds of elections on June 29 and July
6.
</P>
<P>
The Democratic Party, which had been in power for five years,
only won over 30 seats. President Berisha previously said several
times that he would resign if the socialists won the elections.
