<HEADLINE> Myanmar Plants 37,000 Hectares of Forest Annually </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Starting from 1992-93 fiscal year,
Myanmar has been planting 37,260 hectares of forest yearly,
according to Minister of Forestry Chit Swe.
</P>
<P>
Chit Swe made the remark at a tree planting ceremony Monday in
Shwepyitha township where 9,000 saplings were planted, official
paper The New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
Chit Swe called for effective measures to implement the nine
arid regions greening project.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar is rich in forest reserves with different types of
forest covering about 51 per cent of the country's total land
area.
</P>
</TEXT>
