<HEADLINE> Northeast China To Host International Agricultural Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 8 (Xinhua) -- An international agriculture and
fishery exhibition is scheduled for October 16 to 18 in Dalian, a
coastal city in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
Sponsors of the event include the UN's Food and Agricultural
Organization (FAO), the Chinese Ministry of Agriculture, the Inner
Mongolian Automonous Region in north China, and Liaoning, Jilin,
and Heilongjiang Provinces in the northeast.
</P>
<P>
The three-day event mainly deals with the agriculture of the
three northeast provinces and will feature farm and sideline
products, means of production, advanced farm machinery and
technology, high quality breeding, fodder, fertilizers, and
pesticides.
</P>
<P>
The products of other countries and regions will also be on
display, and it will include agricultural and fishery developments
from the country's other coastal provinces.
</P>
<P>
The FAO will also organize special seminars for the show, which
is expected to help overseas business people increase agricultural
investment in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
The three provinces and the eastern part of Inner Mongolia
cover more than a million square kilometers and have a population
of more than 100 million. The vast area is known as a commodity
grain production base and contributes more than a tenth of the
country's grain output.  
</P>
