<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Violence Increases in Buenos Aires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The number of violent crimes
in Greater Buenos Aires in the past two years has increased by
more than 40 percent, according to a report from the capital's
Security Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, 71,898 crime cases happened with violence and this
figure rose to 101,676 in 1996, said the report published today by
the local press.
</P>
<P>
Criminals are increasingly aggressive and their ages are
becoming younger. About 12 percent of the Greater Buenos Aires
criminals charged are under 17, 26 percent between 18 and 20 and
22 percent between 21 and 25.
</P>
<P>
As for homicides, cases have also increased from 950 in 1994 to
1,179 in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Justice authorities attributed the increase in violence to the
lack of professionalism among young people, and it is more so
among minors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
