<HEADLINE> New Irrigation Project in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The second phase of a project to pump
water from the Yellow River in north China for irrigating
farmland has begun operation in Heyang County, in Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The project began in 1990, funded by a World Bank loan of 1.1
billion yuan (about 120 million US dollars). It is the province's
first large electrical irrigation project funded by the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
It can move 40 cubic meters of water per second and has
provided 300,000 farmers in the region with sufficient water for
drinking and for irrigating 90,000 ha of farmland.  
