<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oldest Married Couple in the World Live in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The world's oldest
married couple are both celebrating their 100th birthday this
year, the newspaper El Nuevo Siglo reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that Rudesindo Montenegro Carvajal and Amparo
Roa, who live just outside the Colombian capital, are the oldest
surviving couple in the world and have been married for 77 years.
</P>
<P>
Montenegro was born on May 8, 1897 in Manta in the Central
department of Cundinamarca while Roa will turn 100 on August 28,
the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The couple, who are second cousins, were married on March 14,
1920 in the San Joaquin church in Manta by Assistant Vicar
Guillermo Garavito.
</P>
<P>
The copy of the marriage certificate issued by the church said
that they were granted a dispensation against marriages between
relatives.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the newspaper, the couple had only one
explanation for their longevity: "God has wanted this to be."
</P>
<P>
One key to their longevity may be in what they eat. Their
youngest son Arsenio said that they have eaten tortillas, cheese,
eggs and peas all their lives.
</P>
<P>
The 100-year old couple have 9 children (a son and a daughter
have died), 45 grandchildren, 55 great grandchildren and 10 great
great grandchildren.
</P>
<P>
They have spent the last 40 years on a small farm in Tabio,
Cundinamarca, west of the capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
