<P>
Li said he is optimistic about the future Sino-US ties, noting
that developing sound bilateral relations is a historic trend that
can not be diverted by the will of any individual.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- State chain stores were encouraged to improve efficiency
and further expand at a national symposium yesterday. The Ministry
of Internal Trade, which oversees the operations of state
businesses, expects to have at least three chain store businesses
with sales volumes exceeding one billion yuan (120 US dollars) by
the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
-- At least eight people were killed and many others injured
over the weekend in Guangdong when floods caused by rainstorms
emerged on the Xijiang and Beijiang, two major tributaries of the
Pearl River.
</P>
<P>
-- About 2.84 million senior high school graduates -- 180,000
more than last year -- are taking the examinations to view for
more than one million seats in 1.035 colleges and universities
across the country.
</P>
<P>
-- China has asked local officials to try harder to find
employment for laid-off workers and guarantee their basic living
standard this year.  
</P>
