<HEADLINE> Greece Pledges to Support Albania Socialists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Greek government today pledged
to support Albania's Socialist Party after it won a landslide
victory in general elections on June 29.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in a telephone conversation, Greek Prime Minister
Costantinos Simitis assured Albania's Socialist Party leader Fatos
Nano that Athens would be "on the side of Albania" and was ready
to provide assistance to help restore order there, acting
government spokesman Nikos Athanasakis said today.
</P>
<P>
Nano informed Simitis that his party had won a two-thirds
majority in the Albanian parliament over President Sali Berisha's
Democratic Party.
</P>
<P>
Greece said recently it hoped the elections in Albania would
result in a government of the widest possible consensus to
undertake the work of restoring order in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian general elections followed a civil conflict
sparked by the collapse of pyramid investment schemes in
January. More than 1,500 people were killed in the clashes.
</P>
