<HEADLINE> Heilongjiang, China's Important Flax Production Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Thanks to favorable conditions,
Heilongjiang province in northeast China has become an important
flax production base, accounting for more than 70 percent of the
nation's flax-growing areas.
</P>
<P>
The province now handles everything in the flax industry
ranging from breeding, growing, fiber processing, and dyeing to
design, scientific research, and marketing.
</P>
<P>
The province now produces 86 percent of the country's flax and
exports 90 percent of its production to 46 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
It has been speeding up technology improvements, in bleaching
and dyeing technology, to catch up with international standards,
and now provides a series of high-quality flax products. 
</P>
