<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tyson Dropped from WBA Ratings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Mike Tyson dropped from the World
Boxing Association ratings Monday after his infamous bitings of
Evander Holyfield's ears in their June 28 bout in Las Vegas.
</P>
<P>
The ratings committee of the Caracas-based WBA said it was
dropping Tyson because according to its regulations no boxer who
has been suspended by a local commission can be rated by the WBA.
</P>
<P>
Tyson has also been suspended by the Nevada State Athletic
Commission.
</P>
<P>
"We are acting in solidarity with the commission of Las Vegas,"
said Alberto Sarmiento, one of the seven members of the committee.
</P>
<P>
The former champion's biting "was an illegal act, like poking a
finger in the eye, and deserves to be sanctioned," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said Tyson could be reinstated in the rankings if the Nevada
commission ends his suspension.
</P>
<P>
South African boxer Franz Botha was promoted to the No. 1
challenger's spot. 
</P>
</TEXT>
