<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Police Report 94 Homicides In Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Costa Rican police reported 94
homicides in the first half of this year, the Cosa Rican Judicial
Investigation Organization (OIJ) announced today.
</P>
<P>
San Jose had the largest number of murders with 49, followed by
Limon, a city 131 kilometers east of the capital with 17, while
Heredia was the city with the least violence with 4 murders, the
OIJ said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
One of the most disturbing crimes in Costa Rica was the murder
of Kristal Autiel Fernandez, a seven-year-old girl who was killed
in a hotel in the capital city on January 19.
</P>
<P>
Of the 94 homicides reported between January and June, 50 were
caused by firearms.
</P>
<P>
According to police statistics, homicides doubled in Costa Rica
during the first half of this decade.
</P>
<P>
Public Security Minister Laura Chinchilla attributed the higher
crime rate to the enormous numbers of firearms in the hands of
citizens.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rican Sociologist Rocio Fernandez believes that the
economic crisis and the disintegration of families are the most
important reasons for the increase in violence in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
