<HEADLINE> Ukrainian Politicians Praise Hong Kong's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's return to China is an
enormous success for China's foreign policy, Vladisslav Shednev,
chairman of the All Ukrainian Center of the Chinese Language was
quoted as saying by the press today.
</P>
<P>
Praising the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping's concept of
"one country, two systems," Shednev said that Deng's use of
peaceful means to get Hong Kong back was a great contribution to
global stability.
</P>
<P>
"If the 'one country, two systems' principle succeeds in China,
it will be the first time in history for two different political
systems to exist in one country," the chairman added.
</P>
<P>
Mikhail Pavlovsky, chairman of the Ukrainian-Chinese Friendship
Committee of the Ukrainian parliament, said Hong Kong's return is
not only the restoration of justice, but also a great achievement
for China's foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
"I hope the whole China will be reunited soon" and "a united
China will become the economic center of East Asia," Pavlovsky
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
