<HEADLINE> Kipketer Equals World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Wilson Kipketer of Denmark
equalled the 800m world record at a athletics meeting here on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan-born runner was clocked one minute and 41.73 seconds
to equall the world mark which was set by Britain's Sebastian Coe
in 1981.
</P>
<P>
But he had to wait for a nail biting two minutes before
discovering if he had matched Coe's mark when the clock originally
showed his time as 1: 41.74 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Coe set the record at Firenze on June 10, 1981. 
