<HEADLINE> Northeast China Increasing Help for Poverty-stricken Farmers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The 600,000 poverty-stricken
farmers in northeast China's Liaoning Province will be able to
escape poverty by the end of the year thanks to local government
efforts.
</P>
<P>
The province started a "help the poor" campaign 11 years ago,
and by now the number of people living in poverty in the province
has gone from 3.6 million in 1986 to 600,000 at present.
</P>
<P>
A local science official says that the province has had more
than 400 scientific and technological projects to help farmers
develop natural resources and industrial production.
</P>
<P>
Fuxin County has collected 50 million yuan for more than 50
technology-promotion projects, and 350,000 farmers have received
technical training.
</P>
<P>
The province has also sent 200 experts to rural areas to help
the farmers escape poverty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
