<HEADLINE> Round-The-Clock Help Center for Citizens of Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- China's first center providing
help to anyone 24 hours a day opened recently in the Luwan
district of Shanghai, the country's largest commercial center.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhu Ru'an, who is in charge of the center, it
handles all manner of daily troubles, and providing advice and a
helping hand for anyone with any kind of problem.
</P>
<P>
The center is getting support from more than 30 government
departments, and 30 organizations, companies, and units.
</P>
<P>
So far, it has received 976 calls for help, every one of which
was successfully dealt with.
</P>
<P>
"The quality of life of people is the best gauge of our work,"
said Li Liangyuan, secretary of the Chinese Communist Party Luwan
District Committee, "so we must satisfy them." 
</P>
