<HEADLINE> New York Technology Shares Set New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Big-name technology shares led the
Nasdaq market in New York to another new high, but stocks ended
mostly lower today as investors secured some profits from last
week's record-setting advance.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average fell 37.32 points to 7,858.49.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 3.11 to 1,470.72 for its third
straight record finish.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a slim margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, with volume reaching 518.78 million
shares as against 370.05 million in Thursday's shortened
pre-holiday session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 4.72 to 912.20, the
NYSE composite index fell 2.13 to 475.55; and the American Stock
Exchange composite index fell 2.37 to 631.97. All three measures
closed at record highs Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Dow was pressured throughout the session by American
Express, which gave back more than half of Thursday's nearly
7-point gain. 
</P>
